    en: "An injured worker with an open NY workers comp case can close the case in exchange for a lump sum from the insurance carrier. NY Workers Compensation Law section 32 governs these settlements. The Workers Compensation Board must approve. The settlement can close the wage-replacement (indemnity) part, the medical part, or both. Once approved, the settlement is final — the worker cannot reopen the case for more benefits even if the injury gets worse later. For workers on Medicare or about to qualify, federal rules require a Medicare Set-Aside (MSA) to protect future medical coverage. Attorney fees are capped at 15 percent of the settlement and require Board approval."
